INSERT INTO movies VALUES('{"title":"Kit Kittredge: An American Girl","year":2008,"cast":["Abigail Breslin","Julia Ormond","Chris O''Donnell","Joan Cusack","Stanley Tucci","Max Thieriot","Jane Krakowski","Madison Davenport","Zach Mills","Austin MacDonald","Willow Smith","Wallace Shawn","Glenne Headly","Colin Mochrie","Kenneth Welsh","Brieanne Jensen","Erin Hilgartner","Dylan Scott Smith"],"genres":["Comedy","Drama"],"href":"Kit_Kittredge:_An_American_Girl","extract":"Kit Kittredge: An American Girl is a 2008 American comedy-drama film directed by Patricia Rozema and written by Ann Peacock, based on the Kit Kittredge stories by Valerie Tripp. The film focuses on the American Girl character Kit Kittredge who lives in Cincinnati, Ohio during the Great Depression.","thumbnail":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/9/93/Kitposter.jpg","thumbnail_width":260,"thumbnail_height":383}');
